metadata.name: 0xSiebe #1
metadata.description: 0xSiebe is a series exploring gradients, layers and grids. It builds on my ever evolving grid framework and it is my first collection that makes use of shaders. Inspiration I got from artists like Martin Grasser and from my general fascination of light and soft colors.

metadata.name: Planet Panels #18
metadata.description:
Stylised isometric terrain with a shifting hand-drawn aesthetic. 

Press any key to toggle black background.

Fully deterministic but the higher your viewport the more terrain will be drawn, this is preferable to fixed scaling.

metadata.name: Lemon Princess #288
metadata.description:
After accidentally swigging from a potion of banishment (mistaking it for her moon mead) at the Annual Wizard’s Gala, Lemon Princess was instantly transformed into a colorful and rapidly modulating energy node.

For a few short moments her karmic fabric strained against extinction. It summoned every possible objection and gripped every precious memory, but alas the brew was too potent and the Princess winked out of existence never to be seen again.

To view each of Lemon Princess' final moments in context (& export them as GIFS) visit:

https://presstube.com/lemon-princess

❤️ @presstube

metadata.name: Luminaries #26
metadata.description:
There is no light without dark.

Luminaries is a study in symmetry, contrast and flow, with a palette inspired by the twelve full moon names. Owning a Luminary enables you to request a signed print for an additional fee. 

You can learn more about features and prints at: https://www.phaust.art/luminary

Each Luminary is composed of moons in various phases. Their layout derived from a handful of geometries. They contrast with their surroundings: filled with glittering stars, inky strokes or solid colour. 

Backgrounds can split along lines of symmetry – with dark and light contrasting as strokes seamlessly flow across the two halves. 

Luminaries are alive. They’re in retrograde once a month, a day in which you’ll see yours in a new light.

------

Collection Size: 158. One for each of the confirmed moons in our solar system.

Palettes: 12 + 1. One for each of the full moons plus a rarer secret palette: Wolf, Snow, Worm, Pink, Flower, Strawberry, Buck, Sturgeon, Harvest, Hunter, Beaver, Cold, ????.

Retrograde: day of the month that your Luminary will change for one day only.

S: to save at high resolution. 

Prints: request from https://www.phaust.art/luminary

metadata.name: The Imaginary River Of Thoughts #8
metadata.description:
This work was inspired by the analogy of the mind that is similar to a river. Where all thoughts flow endlessly following the current within an imaginary landscape.

The visual representation of this work came from a personal reflection on human perspectives in measuring a decision within their everyday lives.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the screen capture.

Made using Hydra (https://hydra.ojack.xyz/)

Rangga Purnama Aji, 2022
https://linktr.ee/ranggapuraji

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 3 #497
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ - Iteration 1, ____ - Iteration 2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.
